\begin_body

\begin_layout Chapter
Background 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The Chapter 2 provides the background context, in order to clarify the key
 elements to understand this project.
 This chapter contains three major parts, Thesis motivation, Economical
 context and Technical context.
 Getting through the first part of the chapter 2, it will be understood
 what are those factors that made the motivation of this thesis and then
 in next part, it will be shown how is internet economical environment and
 in the final part the technical context will be shown.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Section
Thesis motivations
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The motivation of this project consist of three main factors: Existing Demand,Ad
vertisement and Data Decentralization.
 Each of them play important rules to illustrate the main will for done
 this thesis and why it is chosen.
 The following show the details regarding each factors.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsection
Existing Demand
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Where there is no need, there is no users.
 If there is no users , there is no market.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Here is a survey research analysis trying to identify user behavior.
 The survey research was a part of the project realized in the frame of
 Quality Management and Experimental Software Engineering classes at Poznan
 University of Technology.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Objectives
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The objectives is to get information about habits of people watching videos
 in order to help the production of a video platform software.
 The focus of the survey is targets user's habits to know how to fit their
 expectations.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Design of the Survey
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The study was designed as successive independent sample.
 It was decided to administer the survey to the participants in the following
 ways:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Same way of questioning to participants (different people from random samples
 of a population).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
The answer should not differ with the time for a same person.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
Release with a Google form ( e.g.
 appendix ).
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize
35 participants.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection
Survey questions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
As it been told before, these questions were designed to illustrate the
 behavior (need,habit) of users in order to help the definition of development
 backlogs.
 The questions and related results are as up coming paragraphs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
What device(s) are you using the most?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Regarding the devices used, the TV, cable and satellite are not used ( e.g.
 Appendix ).
 The computer is the most used device.
 A desktop application look like a good choice to develop the application.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The mobile is represented as well and its market is growing fast ( source
 ).
 It would be interesting to develop a web application or some technology
 easing the move to a browser application or a mobile application for future
 developments like Javascript or Java (native on Android).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\align center
\begin_inset Graphics
	filename /Volumes/SHIVA/lyx/master-thesis_hancquart-12_9/Q1.png

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Plain Layout
\begin_inset Caption Standard

\begin_layout Plain Layout
Q1
\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Paragraph
When are you usually watching videos?
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
According to the results, a big part of the videos will be watched around
 during the same time.
 More than 85% are watching videos on the same period of the day (Evening,
 Night).
 Considering this, it is worth to focus on a technology able to take advantage
 of a it to decrease the data transfer.
 Thinking of a decentralized application, the memory of each user could
 be used to perform request of other users on the hard-drive ( unicast )
 or to focus on the currently most watched videos ( broadcast / multicast
 ).
 Broadcast, multicast and unicast connections options should be explored
 and compared.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Float figure
wide false
sideways false
status collapsed

