\begin_layout Standard
Video commerce is using the video content to benefit,sell and support commercial
 goods or services on internet.
 No matter what, the video downloaded or streamed, it often contains clickable
 link which can open up a web or transaction procedure.
 Moreover, the clickable objects may not always be within the video itself,
 but part of the Flash or HTML5 player used to play back the video.
 The term vCommerce was first time used by ShopNBC (a.k.a.
 ValueVision - VVTV) in the summer of 2007 as part of the launch of ShopNBC.TV.
